stats/web?componentName=critic-score-summary&componentDisplayName=Critic+Score+Summary&componentType=MetaScoreSummary",{"componentName":3007,"componentDisplayName":3008,"componentType":3009},"critic-score-summary","Critic Score Summary","MetaScoreSummary",{"data":3011,"links":3178,"meta":3190},{"id":1648,"totalResults":2177,"item":3012},{"default":3013,"positive":3088,"negative":3142,"neutral":3143},[3014,3026,3036,3047,3057,3068,3078],{"quote":3015,"score":38,"url":3016,"date":3017,"author":3018,"authorSlug":3019,"image":1288,"publicationName":3020,"publicationSlug":3021,"reviewedProduct":3022},"There’s never a false note from the young actors, all of whom have deeply moving scenes. But Young Mothers is also captivating when it’s simply taking in the quotidian responsibilities of new parenthood — feeding, diaper changing, bathtime — or when it catches an expression of wonder or joy as a mother gazes into the tiny face of the child she has created.","https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/young-mothers-review-dardenne-brothers-1236229419/","2025-05-30","David Rooney","david-rooney","The Hollywood Reporter","the-hollywood-reporter",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3025},"movies","/movie/young-mothers/",{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3027,"score":22,"url":3028,"date":3029,"author":3030,"authorSlug":3031,"image":1288,"publicationName":3032,"publicationSlug":3033,"reviewedProduct":3034},"Because of the ensemble structure, each tale is interrupted by another, so “Young Mothers” lacks some of the suspense that powers many of the Dardennes’ other films. Yet that slower pace allows a tenderness to develop, and the tension between the girls’ youth and newfound maternal instincts to emerge. ","https://www.nytimes.com/2026/01/08/movies/young-mothers-review.html","2026-01-08","Alissa Wilkinson","alissa-wilkinson","The New York Times","the-new-york-times",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3035},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3037,"score":3038,"url":3039,"date":3040,"author":3041,"authorSlug":3042,"image":1288,"publicationName":3043,"publicationSlug":3044,"reviewedProduct":3045},"There is a satisfying, compact completeness to their handling of the storylines of four different young mothers and sufficient grace notes are enabled in each case to stave off the cliches that occasionally threaten to engulf events.",83,"https://www.indiewire.com/criticism/movies/young-mothers-review-dardennes-1235126057/","2025-05-23","Sophie Monks Kaufman","sophie-monks-kaufman","IndieWire","indiewire",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3046},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3048,"score":2175,"url":3049,"date":3050,"author":3051,"authorSlug":3052,"image":1288,"publicationName":3053,"publicationSlug":3054,"reviewedProduct":3055},"The strain of absent fathers, generational addiction and the cycle of poverty are carefully countered by resilience, love and the flicker of youthful possibility.","https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/film/review/2025/08/27/young-mothers-review-the-dardenne-brothers-bring-empathy-to-interlocking-stories-of-underage-mothers-in-liege/","2025-08-28","Tara Brady","tara-brady","The Irish Times","the-irish-times",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3056},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3058,"score":3059,"url":3060,"date":3061,"author":3062,"authorSlug":3063,"image":1288,"publicationName":3064,"publicationSlug":3065,"reviewedProduct":3066},"Young Mothers is a welcome return to form for the Dardenne brothers, balancing social observation with character study.\r\n",75,"https://www.slantmagazine.com/film/young-mothers-review-jean-pierre-luc-dardenne/","2026-01-05","Jake Cole","jake-cole","Slant Magazine","slant-magazine",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3067},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3069,"score":1282,"url":3070,"date":3071,"author":3072,"authorSlug":3073,"image":1288,"publicationName":3074,"publicationSlug":3075,"reviewedProduct":3076},"After so many punishing stories, most recently 2022​’s Tori and Lokita, it’s hard to begrudge them the raw sentiment and mostly happy, hopeful endings of their newest one. But it comes too easy, in a film so artfully and opportunistically structured, which jumps from dramatic peak to dramatic peak as if skipping tracks on an album.","https://lwlies.com/reviews/young-mothers","2025-09-01","Mark Asch","mark-asch","Little White Lies","little-white-lies",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3077},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3079,"score":40,"url":3080,"date":3081,"author":3082,"authorSlug":3083,"image":1288,"publicationName":3084,"publicationSlug":3085,"reviewedProduct":3086},"Rather than individuals facing all-too-common yet rarely portrayed challenges, the characters here seem little more than pawns in a predictable game, whose conclusion is never in doubt.","https://theplaylist.net/the-young-mothers-home-review-the-dardennes-in-polyphonic-mode-largely-ring-false-cannes-20250529/","2025-06-05","Elena Lazic","elena-lazic","The Playlist","the-playlist",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3087},{"url":2174,"score":2175},[3089,3092,3101,3111,3120,3123,3132],{"quote":3015,"score":38,"url":3016,"date":3017,"author":3018,"authorSlug":3019,"image":1288,"publicationName":3020,"publicationSlug":3021,"reviewedProduct":3090},{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3091},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3093,"score":38,"url":3094,"date":3040,"author":3095,"authorSlug":3096,"image":1288,"publicationName":3097,"publicationSlug":3098,"reviewedProduct":3099},"There is such simplicity and clarity here, an honest apportioning of dignity and intelligence to everyone on screen: every scene and every character portrait is unforced and unembellished. The straightforward assertion of hope through giving help and asking for help is very powerful.\r\n\r\n","https://www.theguardian.com/film/2025/may/23/jeunes-meres-the-young-mothers-home-review-dardennes-brothers","Peter Bradshaw","peter-bradshaw","The Guardian","the-guardian",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3100},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3102,"score":22,"url":3103,"date":3104,"author":3105,"authorSlug":3106,"image":1288,"publicationName":3107,"publicationSlug":3108,"reviewedProduct":3109},"The Dardennes’ movies have a gentle uniformity, which is why they often slip through the cracks among flashier pictures vying for our attention. But Young Mothers is among the best of their films, so empathetically understated that its full power may not hit you until hours after you’ve watched it. ","https://time.com/7345054/young-mothers-review/","2026-01-12","Stephanie Zacharek","stephanie-zacharek","Time","time",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3110},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3112,"score":22,"url":3113,"date":3104,"author":3114,"authorSlug":3115,"image":1288,"publicationName":3116,"publicationSlug":3117,"reviewedProduct":3118},"Understated, graceful, and moving, it’s the first great film of 2026.","https://www.thedailybeast.com/obsessed/young-mothers-review-the-first-great-film-of-2026/","Nick Schager","nick-schager","The Daily Beast","the-daily-beast",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3119},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3027,"score":22,"url":3028,"date":3029,"author":3030,"authorSlug":3031,"image":1288,"publicationName":3032,"publicationSlug":3033,"reviewedProduct":3121},{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3122},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3124,"score":22,"url":3125,"date":3040,"author":3126,"authorSlug":3127,"image":1288,"publicationName":3128,"publicationSlug":3129,"reviewedProduct":3130},"Deeply moving but never manipulative, Young Mothers amounts to the brothers’ best film in more than a decade.","https://variety.com/2025/film/reviews/young-mothers-review-jeune-meres-1236407593/","Peter Debruge","peter-debruge","Variety","variety",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3131},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3133,"score":3134,"url":3135,"date":1654,"author":3136,"authorSlug":3137,"image":1288,"publicationName":3138,"publicationSlug":3139,"reviewedProduct":3140},"The film is deeply sympathetic to the impossibly difficult choices these girls face and respectful of their efforts to do better for their babies than their parents did for them.",88,"https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/young-mothers-dardenne-brothers-film-review-2026","Nell Minow","nell-minow","RogerEbert.com","rogerebertcom",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3141},{"url":2174,"score":2175},[],[3144,3153,3156,3166,3175],{"quote":3145,"score":1282,"url":3146,"date":1654,"author":3147,"authorSlug":3148,"image":1288,"publicationName":3149,"publicationSlug":3150,"reviewedProduct":3151},"Arguably, there’s nothing innately wrong with Young Mothers, other than it feeling like a return to safer socio-cultural predicaments which characterized the directors’ earlier output, which often involved children.","https://www.ioncinema.com/reviews/dardenne-jeunes-meres-young-mothers-movie-review","Nicholas Bell","nicholas-bell","IONCINEMA.com","ioncinemacom",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3152},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3069,"score":1282,"url":3070,"date":3071,"author":3072,"authorSlug":3073,"image":1288,"publicationName":3074,"publicationSlug":3075,"reviewedProduct":3154},{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3155},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3157,"score":1282,"url":3158,"date":3159,"author":3160,"authorSlug":3161,"image":1288,"publicationName":3162,"publicationSlug":3163,"reviewedProduct":3164},"Where a lesser film could fall into feeling like it is just hitting issues without exploring them, Young Mothers always grounds the bigger issues in real characters. It finds genuine emotion in capturing how this is not something abstract, but a reality with which they’ll have to contend. ","https://www.thewrap.com/young-mothers-review-dardenne-brothers-cannes/","2025-05-24","Chase Hutchinson","chase-hutchinson","TheWrap","thewrap",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3165},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3167,"score":1282,"url":3168,"date":3040,"author":3169,"authorSlug":3170,"image":1288,"publicationName":3171,"publicationSlug":3172,"reviewedProduct":3173},"It’s a decent film about an underexplored subject and adequately acted by a cast of inexperienced unknowns, but nothing we haven’t seen before from the determinedly low-key Dardennes. ","https://www.thetimes.com/culture/film/article/cannes-film-festival-2025-reviews-best-worst-cd0mhgvqk","Ed Potton","ed-potton","The Times","the-times",{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3174},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"quote":3079,"score":40,"url":3080,"date":3081,"author":3082,"authorSlug":3083,"image":1288,"publicationName":3084,"publicationSlug":3085,"reviewedProduct":3176},{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024,"criticScoreSummary":3177},{"url":2174,"score":2175},{"self":3179,"tabs":3181},{"href":3180},"https://backend.metacritic.com/reviews/metacritic/critic/movies/young-mothers/summary/web?componentName=critic-reviews&componentDisplayName=Critic+Reviews&componentType=ProductReviewsSummary",[3182,3184,3186,3188],{"label":3183,"href":2255},"All Reviews",{"label":3185,"href":2255},"Positive Reviews",{"label":3187,"href":2255},"Mixed Reviews",{"label":3189,"href":2255},"Negative Reviews",{"componentName":3191,"componentDisplayName":3192,"componentType":3193},"critic-reviews","Critic Reviews","ProductReviewsSummary",{"data":3195,"links":3199,"meta":3202},{"item":3196},{"id":3197,"max":2961,"score":2523,"reviewCount":859,"positiveCount":395,"neutralCount":42,"negativeCount":15,"sentiment":2179,"url":3198},"2000561103","/movie/young-mothers/user-reviews/",{"self":3200},{"href":3201},"https://backend.metacritic.com/reviews/metacritic/user/movies/young-mothers/stats/web?componentName=user-score-summary&componentDisplayName=User+Score+Summary&componentType=MetaScoreSummary",{"componentName":3203,"componentDisplayName":3204,"componentType":3009},"user-score-summary","User Score Summary",{"data":3206,"links":3221,"meta":3229},{"id":3197,"totalResults":1120,"item":3207},{"default":3208,"positive":3216,"negative":3217,"neutral":3218},[3209],{"id":3210,"quote":3211,"score":237,"thumbsUp":1288,"thumbsDown":1288,"date":3212,"author":3213,"version":3214,"spoiler":1030,"reviewedProduct":3215},"33901ab3-52b3-4b78-a280-2d13aa673dee","(Mauro Lanari) \nThe dry, stark, hard-edged realism of everyday life, almost documentary-like in style (handheld camerawork, absence of non-diegetic music, often non-professional actors), is the hallmark the Dardenne brothers stubbornly cling to regardless of the sociological subject at hand. And no, it's not always the optimal choice. In this film, for instance, some emotions feel authentic while others come across as mechanical and contrived. \"It's precisely on such a fault line between genuine inspiration and worn-out convention that 'Jeunes Mères' positions itself, likely lauded on the Croisette well beyond its actual merits\" (Raffaele Meale), complete with \"dramaturgical lapses and an energy that gradually dissipates, rendering Cannes' Best Screenplay prize baffling\" (Davide Turrini). The very recent Censis report confirms that fewer than three couples out of ten now have children (29.2%), and that the average age of mothers at the birth of their first child has risen to 31.9 years: realities that barely penetrate the ivory tower in which cinema has shut itself away in France as in Belgium or, conversely, the supposed global panacea of a quintet of fifteen-year-old girls and not a single abortion? Alessandra De Luca (\"Avvenire\") and Franco Lorusso (\"L'Osservatore Romano\") applaud thunderously.","2026-05-09","Mauro_Lanari",1778364283422,{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024},[],[],[3219],{"id":3210,"quote":3211,"score":237,"thumbsUp":1288,"thumbsDown":1288,"date":3212,"author":3213,"version":3214,"spoiler":1030,"reviewedProduct":3220},{"id":1648,"type":3023,"title":1650,"url":3024},{"self":3222,"tabs":3224},{"href":3223},"https://backend.metacritic.com/reviews/metacritic/user/movies/young-mothers/summary/web?componentName=user-reviews&componentDisplayName=User+Reviews&componentType=ProductReviewsSummary",[3225,3226,3227,3228],{"label":3183,"href":2255},{"label":3185,"href":2255},{"label":3187,"href":2255},{"label":3189,"href":2255},{"componentName":3230,"componentDisplayName":3231,"componentType":3193},"user-reviews","User Reviews",{"edition":1287,"title":3233,"id":3197,"slug":1652,"category":1288,"description":1651,"pageType":2225,"section":1288,"image":3234,"typeName":1649,"genres":3236,"themes":3237,"publishers":3238,"score":3239},"Young Mothers Reviews",{"id":1658,"filename":1659,"dateCreated":3235,"alt":1288,"credits":1288,"path":1288,"cropGravity":1288,"crop":1288,"caption":1288,"typeName":1677,"imageUrl":1288,"width":1662,"height":1663,"sType":1288,"bucketType":1664,"bucketPath":1665,"mediaType":1288,"provider":1666},{"date":1288,"timezone":1288},[2194],[2181,2182,2183,2184,2185,2186,2187,2188,2189,2190],[1683,1686,1689,1692,1695,1698,1701,1704,1707,1710,1713,1716,1719,1722,1725,1728,1731,1735,1739,1742,1745,1745,1750,1753,1756,1759,1762,1765,1768,1753,1773,1776,1780],"80",["Reactive",3241],{"$si18n:cached-locale-configs":3242,"$si18n:resolved-locale":2255,"$stoasts":3245},{"en":3243},{"fallbacks":3244,"cacheable":1030},[],[],["Set"],["ShallowReactive",3248],{"fandom-ads-ad-engine-config":-1,"loadPage:skeleton:web:":-1,"loadPage:movies:young-mothers:":-1},"SLiP19d2e